    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Flooring</title>
        <para>The school bus flooring may vary in color and material type per the requirements of the school district.
            The center aisle is a raised surface type tread to eliminate possible slipping in the walkway area. The
            entrance area and step well are also a tread style flooring. The wheel well covers are a black composite
            molded material (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f4700363">Figure 63, Item 2</hotlnk>) with the heater hoses enclosed in the outer section (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f4700363">Figure 63, Item 3</hotlnk>) of the wheel well against the bus wall. Drawing "A"
            represents rear wheel well cover (old style) and "B" represents front and rear wheel well covers (new
            style).
        </para>
        <figure id="f4700363" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic id="g4700363.webp" filename="../figg47/G4700363.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 63. Wheel Well Cover</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">CHAIR MOUNTING RAIL</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">WHEEL WELL COVER</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">MOLDED HEATER HOSE COVER INTEGRAL WITH WHEEL WELL COVER</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">HEATER HOSE COVER ALONG BUS WALL</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">BUS FLOOR COVERING</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">WHEEL WELL COVER MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
